.SH SHCrossPowerDensityLC
.PP
Compute the cross-power spectral density of two complex functions for a
single spherical harmonic degree.
.SH Usage
.PP
\f[C]cpsd\f[R] = SHCrossPowerDensityLC (\f[C]cilm1\f[R],
\f[C]cilm2\f[R], \f[C]l\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
.B \f[C]cpsd\f[R] : output, complex(dp)
The cross-power spectral density of the two complex functions for
spherical harmonic degree \f[C]l\f[R].
.TP
.B \f[C]cilm1\f[R] : input, complex*16, dimension (2, \f[C]lmaxin1\f[R]+1, \f[C]lmaxin1\f[R]+1)
The first complex function expressed in complex spherical harmonics.
.TP
.B \f[C]cilm2\f[R] : input, complex*16, dimension (2, \f[C]lmaxin2\f[R]+1, \f[C]lmaxin2\f[R]+1)
The second complex function expressed in complex spherical harmonics.
.TP
.B \f[C]l\f[R] : input, integer
The spherical harmonic degree.
This must be less than or equal to the minimum of \f[C]lmaxin1\f[R] and
\f[C]lmaxin2\f[R].
.SH Description
.PP
\f[C]SHCrossPowerDensityLC\f[R] will calculate the cross-power spectral
density of two complex functions expressed in complex 4-pi normalized
spherical harmonics for a single spherical harmonic degree \f[C]l\f[R].
This is calculated as:
.PP
\f[C]cpsd = Sum_{i=1}\[ha]2 Sum_{m=0}\[ha]l cilm1(i, l+1, m+1) * conjg[cilm2(i, l+1, m+1)] / (2l + 1)\f[R].
